FT  12 JUN 93 / World News in Brief: Market pins hopes on base rates cut
This week has seen a recovery of 31.9 points in the FT-SE 100 index, fuelled
largely by hopes that chancellor Kenneth Clarke will sanction a cut in base
rates in his Mansion House speech to the City on Tuesday. The index closed
last night at 2,861.8, up 1.8 on the day after moderate trading. London
Stock Exchange, Page 17; Lex, Page 26
